{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":381,"text":"\"Even in purely non-religious terms,"},{"time":4604,"text":"homosexuality represents a misuse of the sexual faculty."},{"time":10659,"text":"It is a pathetic little second-rate substitute for reality --"},{"time":15285,"text":"a pitiable flight from life."},{"time":17685,"text":"As such, it deserves no compassion,"},{"time":21508,"text":"it deserves no treatment"},{"time":24070,"text":"as minority martyrdom,"},{"time":26837,"text":"and it deserves not to be deemed anything but a pernicious sickness.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":33515,"text":"That's from Time magazine in 1966, when I was three years old."},{"time":38737,"text":"And last year, the president of the United States"},{"time":42651,"text":"came out in favor of gay marriage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45234,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52683,"text":"And my question is, how did we get from there to here?"},{"time":58385,"text":"How did an illness become an identity?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63125,"text":"When I was perhaps six years old,"},{"time":66085,"text":"I went to a shoe store with my mother and my brother."},{"time":69018,"text":"And at the end of buying our shoes,"},{"time":71425,"text":"the salesman said to us that we could each have a balloon to take home."},{"time":75217,"text":"My brother wanted a red balloon, and I wanted a pink balloon."},{"time":80883,"text":"My mother said that she thought I'd really rather have a blue balloon."},{"time":85798,"text":"But I said that I definitely wanted the pink one."},{"time":88934,"text":"And she reminded me that my favorite color was blue."},{"time":94353,"text":"The fact that my favorite color now is blue, but I'm still gay --"},{"time":99143,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":102251,"text":"is evidence of both my mother's influence and its limits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106623,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108690,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115557,"text":"When I was little, my mother used to say,"},{"time":118114,"text":"\"The love you have for your children is like no other feeling in the world."},{"time":122650,"text":"And until you have children, you don't know what it's like.\""},{"time":125995,"text":"And when I was little, I took it as the greatest compliment in the world"},{"time":129189,"text":"that she would say that about parenting my brother and me."},{"time":132009,"text":"And when I was an adolescent, I thought"},{"time":134637,"text":"that I'm gay, and so I probably can't have a family."},{"time":138001,"text":"And when she said it, it made me anxious."},{"time":140378,"text":"And after I came out of the closet,"},{"time":141904,"text":"when she continued to say it, it made me furious."},{"time":145104,"text":"I said, \"I'm gay. That's not the direction that I'm headed in."},{"time":149245,"text":"And I want you to stop saying that.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":155013,"text":"About 20 years ago, I was asked by my editors at The New York Times Magazine"},{"time":160070,"text":"to write a piece about deaf culture."},{"time":162511,"text":"And I was rather taken aback."},{"time":164348,"text":"I had thought of deafness entirely as an illness."},{"time":166543,"text":"Those poor people, they couldn't hear."},{"time":168269,"text":"They lacked hearing, and what could we do for them?"},{"time":171043,"text":"And then I went out into the deaf world."},{"time":173160,"text":"I went to deaf clubs."},{"time":175551,"text":"I saw performances of deaf theater and of deaf poetry."},{"time":179471,"text":"I even went to the Miss Deaf America contest in Nashville, Tennessee"},{"time":185682,"text":"where people complained about that slurry Southern signing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189526,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":193782,"text":"And as I plunged deeper and deeper into the deaf world,"},{"time":197709,"text":"I become convinced that deafness was a culture"},{"time":200715,"text":"and that the people in the deaf world who said,"},{"time":203077,"text":"\"We don't lack hearing, we have membership in a culture,\""},{"time":206444,"text":"were saying something that was viable."},{"time":209021,"text":"It wasn't my culture,"},{"time":210526,"text":"and I didn't particularly want to rush off and join it,"},{"time":213244,"text":"but I appreciated that it was a culture"},{"time":216075,"text":"and that for the people who were members of it,"},{"time":218210,"text":"it felt as valuable as Latino culture or gay culture or Jewish culture."},{"time":224499,"text":"It felt as valid perhaps even as American culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229499,"text":"Then a friend of a friend of mine had a daughter who was a dwarf."},{"time":232913,"text":"And when her daughter was born,"},{"time":234392,"text":"she suddenly found herself confronting questions"},{"time":236723,"text":"that now began to seem quite resonant to me."},{"time":239510,"text":"She was facing the question of what to do with this child."},{"time":243377,"text":"Should she say, \"You're just like everyone else but a little bit shorter?\""},{"time":246837,"text":"Or should she try to construct some kind of dwarf identity,"},{"time":250052,"text":"get involved in the Little People of America,"},{"time":252599,"text":"become aware of what was happening for dwarfs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255392,"text":"And I suddenly thought,"},{"time":256993,"text":"most deaf children are born to hearing parents."},{"time":259212,"text":"Those hearing parents tend to try to cure them."},{"time":262011,"text":"Those deaf people discover community somehow in adolescence."},{"time":266177,"text":"Most gay people are born to straight parents."},{"time":268526,"text":"Those straight parents often want them to function"},{"time":270974,"text":"in what they think of as the mainstream world,"},{"time":273244,"text":"and those gay people have to discover identity later on."},{"time":276848,"text":"And here was this friend of mine"},{"time":278464,"text":"looking at these questions of identity with her dwarf daughter."},{"time":281793,"text":"And I thought, there it is again:"},{"time":283569,"text":"A family that perceives itself to be normal"},{"time":286135,"text":"with a child who seems to be extraordinary."},{"time":288505,"text":"And I hatched the idea that there are really two kinds of identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293017,"text":"There are vertical identities,"},{"time":294941,"text":"which are passed down generationally from parent to child."},{"time":297923,"text":"Those are things like ethnicity, frequently nationality, language, often religion."},{"time":303526,"text":"Those are things you have in common with your parents and with your children."},{"time":308004,"text":"And while some of them can be difficult,"},{"time":310277,"text":"there's no attempt to cure them."},{"time":312471,"text":"You can argue that it's harder in the United States --"},{"time":315883,"text":"our current presidency notwithstanding --"},{"time":317857,"text":"to be a person of color."},{"time":319690,"text":"And yet, we have nobody who is trying to ensure"},{"time":322389,"text":"that the next generation of children born to African-Americans and Asians"},{"time":326277,"text":"come out with creamy skin and yellow hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329666,"text":"There are these other identities which you have to learn from a peer group."},{"time":333943,"text":"And I call them horizontal identities,"},{"time":336241,"text":"because the peer group is the horizontal experience."},{"time":339136,"text":"These are identities that are alien to your parents"},{"time":341704,"text":"and that you have to discover when you get to see them in peers."},{"time":345889,"text":"And those identities, those horizontal identities,"},{"time":348974,"text":"people have almost always tried to cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352690,"text":"And I wanted to look at what the process is"},{"time":355358,"text":"through which people who have those identities"},{"time":357575,"text":"come to a good relationship with them."},{"time":360303,"text":"And it seemed to me that there were three levels of acceptance"},{"time":364556,"text":"that needed to take place."},{"time":365995,"text":"There's self-acceptance, there's family acceptance, and there's social acceptance."},{"time":371544,"text":"And they don't always coincide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373491,"text":"And a lot of the time, people who have these conditions are very angry"},{"time":377627,"text":"because they feel as though their parents don't love them,"},{"time":380691,"text":"when what actually has happened is that their parents don't accept them."},{"time":384990,"text":"Love is something that ideally is there unconditionally"},{"time":388156,"text":"throughout the relationship between a parent and a child."},{"time":391203,"text":"But acceptance is something that takes time."},{"time":394469,"text":"It always takes time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396704,"text":"One of the dwarfs I got to know was a guy named Clinton Brown."},{"time":401596,"text":"When he was born, he was diagnosed with diastrophic dwarfism,"},{"time":404998,"text":"a very disabling condition,"},{"time":406776,"text":"and his parents were told that he would never walk, he would never talk,"},{"time":410182,"text":"he would have no intellectual capacity,"},{"time":412157,"text":"and he would probably not even recognize them."},{"time":414856,"text":"And it was suggested to them that they leave him at the hospital"},{"time":418277,"text":"so that he could die there quietly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420491,"text":"And his mother said she wasn't going to do it."},{"time":422455,"text":"And she took her son home."},{"time":424222,"text":"And even though she didn't have a lot of educational or financial advantages,"},{"time":427856,"text":"she found the best doctor in the country"},{"time":429804,"text":"for dealing with diastrophic dwarfism,"},{"time":432003,"text":"and she got Clinton enrolled with him."},{"time":434169,"text":"And in the course of his childhood,"},{"time":436250,"text":"he had 30 major surgical procedures."},{"time":439323,"text":"And he spent all this time stuck in the hospital"},{"time":441510,"text":"while he was having those procedures,"},{"time":443203,"text":"as a result of which he now can walk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445611,"text":"And while he was there, they sent tutors around to help him with his school work."},{"time":449961,"text":"And he worked very hard because there was nothing else to do."},{"time":452790,"text":"And he ended up achieving at a level"},{"time":454537,"text":"that had never before been contemplated by any member of his family."},{"time":458112,"text":"He was the first one in his family, in fact, to go to college,"},{"time":461442,"text":"where he lived on campus and drove a specially-fitted car"},{"time":464824,"text":"that accommodated his unusual body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467608,"text":"And his mother told me this story of coming home one day --"},{"time":470571,"text":"and he went to college nearby --"},{"time":472336,"text":"and she said, \"I saw that car, which you can always recognize,"},{"time":475423,"text":"in the parking lot of a bar,\" she said. (Laughter)"},{"time":479846,"text":"\"And I thought to myself, they're six feet tall, he's three feet tall."},{"time":484456,"text":"Two beers for them is four beers for him.\""},{"time":486756,"text":"She said, \"I knew I couldn't go in there and interrupt him,"},{"time":489369,"text":"but I went home, and I left him eight messages on his cell phone.\""},{"time":493557,"text":"She said, \"And then I thought,"},{"time":495042,"text":"if someone had said to me when he was born"},{"time":497142,"text":"that my future worry would be that he'd go drinking and driving with his college buddies -- \""}]},{"cues":[{"time":502755,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511537,"text":"And I said to her, \"What do you think you did"},{"time":513576,"text":"that helped him to emerge as this charming, accomplished, wonderful person?\""},{"time":518036,"text":"And she said, \"What did I do? I loved him, that's all."},{"time":522723,"text":"Clinton just always had that light in him."},{"time":525859,"text":"And his father and I were lucky enough to be the first to see it there.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":532272,"text":"I'm going to quote from another magazine of the '60s."},{"time":535310,"text":"This one is from 1968 -- The Atlantic Monthly, voice of liberal America --"},{"time":541004,"text":"written by an important bioethicist."},{"time":543808,"text":"He said, \"There is no reason to feel guilty"},{"time":547616,"text":"about putting a Down syndrome child away,"},{"time":550921,"text":"whether it is put away in the sense of hidden in a sanitarium"},{"time":555980,"text":"or in a more responsible, lethal sense."},{"time":559889,"text":"It is sad, yes -- dreadful. But it carries no guilt."},{"time":564837,"text":"True guilt arises only from an offense against a person,"},{"time":568937,"text":"and a Down's is not a person.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":573538,"text":"There's been a lot of ink given to the enormous progress that we've made"},{"time":577479,"text":"in the treatment of gay people."},{"time":579606,"text":"The fact that our attitude has changed is in the headlines every day."},{"time":583642,"text":"But we forget how we used to see people who had other differences,"},{"time":588338,"text":"how we used to see people who were disabled,"},{"time":590476,"text":"how inhuman we held people to be."},{"time":593389,"text":"And the change that's been accomplished there,"},{"time":595267,"text":"which is almost equally radical,"},{"time":597093,"text":"is one that we pay not very much attention to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599969,"text":"One of the families I interviewed, Tom and Karen Robards,"},{"time":603921,"text":"were taken aback when, as young and successful New Yorkers,"},{"time":607649,"text":"their first child was diagnosed with Down syndrome."},{"time":611104,"text":"They thought the educational opportunities for him were not what they should be,"},{"time":615190,"text":"and so they decided they would build a little center --"},{"time":619043,"text":"two classrooms that they started with a few other parents --"},{"time":622707,"text":"to educate kids with D.S."},{"time":625170,"text":"And over the years, that center grew into something called the Cooke Center,"},{"time":629070,"text":"where there are now thousands upon thousands"},{"time":631227,"text":"of children with intellectual disabilities who are being taught."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635004,"text":"In the time since that Atlantic Monthly story ran,"},{"time":638142,"text":"the life expectancy for people with Down syndrome has tripled."},{"time":642315,"text":"The experience of Down syndrome people includes those who are actors,"},{"time":647074,"text":"those who are writers, some who are able to live fully independently in adulthood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653127,"text":"The Robards had a lot to do with that."},{"time":655002,"text":"And I said, \"Do you regret it?"},{"time":656536,"text":"Do you wish your child didn't have Down syndrome?"},{"time":659139,"text":"Do you wish you'd never heard of it?\""},{"time":660988,"text":"And interestingly his father said,"},{"time":663355,"text":"\"Well, for David, our son, I regret it,"},{"time":665942,"text":"because for David, it's a difficult way to be in the world,"},{"time":669322,"text":"and I'd like to give David an easier life."},{"time":672070,"text":"But I think if we lost everyone with Down syndrome, it would be a catastrophic loss.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":677170,"text":"And Karen Robards said to me, \"I'm with Tom."},{"time":680601,"text":"For David, I would cure it in an instant to give him an easier life."},{"time":684542,"text":"But speaking for myself -- well, I would never have believed 23 years ago when he was born"},{"time":689978,"text":"that I could come to such a point --"},{"time":691988,"text":"speaking for myself, it's made me so much better and so much kinder"},{"time":696336,"text":"and so much more purposeful in my whole life,"},{"time":699370,"text":"that speaking for myself, I wouldn't give it up for anything in the world.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":705779,"text":"We live at a point when social acceptance for these and many other conditions"},{"time":710164,"text":"is on the up and up."},{"time":711902,"text":"And yet we also live at the moment"},{"time":713738,"text":"when our ability to eliminate those conditions"},{"time":716629,"text":"has reached a height we never imagined before."},{"time":719237,"text":"Most deaf infants born in the United States now"},{"time":722396,"text":"will receive Cochlear implants,"},{"time":724189,"text":"which are put into the brain and connected to a receiver,"},{"time":729004,"text":"and which allow them to acquire a facsimile of hearing and to use oral speech."},{"time":734022,"text":"A compound that has been tested in mice, BMN-111,"},{"time":738321,"text":"is useful in preventing the action of the achondroplasia gene."},{"time":743374,"text":"Achondroplasia is the most common form of dwarfism,"},{"time":746119,"text":"and mice who have been given that substance and who have the achondroplasia gene,"},{"time":750086,"text":"grow to full size."},{"time":752004,"text":"Testing in humans is around the corner."},{"time":754555,"text":"There are blood tests which are making progress"},{"time":756811,"text":"that would pick up Down syndrome more clearly and earlier in pregnancies than ever before,"},{"time":762306,"text":"making it easier and easier for people to eliminate those pregnancies,"},{"time":767550,"text":"or to terminate them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768870,"text":"And so we have both social progress and medical progress."},{"time":773537,"text":"And I believe in both of them."},{"time":775389,"text":"I believe the social progress is fantastic and meaningful and wonderful,"},{"time":779444,"text":"and I think the same thing about the medical progress."},{"time":782540,"text":"But I think it's a tragedy when one of them doesn't see the other."},{"time":786903,"text":"And when I see the way they're intersecting"},{"time":788974,"text":"in conditions like the three I've just described,"},{"time":791188,"text":"I sometimes think it's like those moments in grand opera"},{"time":794838,"text":"when the hero realizes he loves the heroine"},{"time":797442,"text":"at the exact moment that she lies expiring on a divan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801889,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":804688,"text":"We have to think about how we feel about cures altogether."},{"time":808570,"text":"And a lot of the time the question of parenthood is,"},{"time":811436,"text":"what do we validate in our children,"},{"time":813288,"text":"and what do we cure in them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":815040,"text":"Jim Sinclair, a prominent autism activist, said,"},{"time":819211,"text":"\"When parents say 'I wish my child did not have autism,'"},{"time":823865,"text":"what they're really saying is 'I wish the child I have did not exist"},{"time":828724,"text":"and I had a different, non-autistic child instead.'"},{"time":832743,"text":"Read that again. This is what we hear when you mourn over our existence."},{"time":837535,"text":"This is what we hear when you pray for a cure --"},{"time":840737,"text":"that your fondest wish for us"},{"time":842642,"text":"is that someday we will cease to be"},{"time":845021,"text":"and strangers you can love will move in behind our faces.\""},{"time":850576,"text":"It's a very extreme point of view,"},{"time":853642,"text":"but it points to the reality that people engage with the life they have"},{"time":857771,"text":"and they don't want to be cured or changed or eliminated."},{"time":862336,"text":"They want to be whoever it is that they've come to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865556,"text":"One of the families I interviewed for this project"},{"time":869356,"text":"was the family of Dylan Klebold who was one of the perpetrators of the Columbine massacre."},{"time":874610,"text":"It took a long time to persuade them to talk to me,"},{"time":877405,"text":"and once they agreed, they were so full of their story"},{"time":880169,"text":"that they couldn't stop telling it."},{"time":881868,"text":"And the first weekend I spent with them -- the first of many --"},{"time":884485,"text":"I recorded more than 20 hours of conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887606,"text":"And on Sunday night, we were all exhausted."},{"time":889869,"text":"We were sitting in the kitchen. Sue Klebold was fixing dinner."},{"time":892755,"text":"And I said, \"If Dylan were here now,"},{"time":895276,"text":"do you have a sense of what you'd want to ask him?\""},{"time":898121,"text":"And his father said, \"I sure do."},{"time":900489,"text":"I'd want to ask him what the hell he thought he was doing.\""},{"time":904038,"text":"And Sue looked at the floor, and she thought for a minute."},{"time":907676,"text":"And then she looked back up and said,"},{"time":909855,"text":"\"I would ask him to forgive me for being his mother"},{"time":913918,"text":"and never knowing what was going on inside his head.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":918342,"text":"When I had dinner with her a couple of years later --"},{"time":921310,"text":"one of many dinners that we had together --"},{"time":923237,"text":"she said, \"You know, when it first happened,"},{"time":926647,"text":"I used to wish that I had never married, that I had never had children."},{"time":930455,"text":"If I hadn't gone to Ohio State and crossed paths with Tom,"},{"time":933947,"text":"this child wouldn't have existed and this terrible thing wouldn't have happened."},{"time":937589,"text":"But I've come to feel that I love the children I had so much"},{"time":942104,"text":"that I don't want to imagine a life without them."},{"time":945407,"text":"I recognize the pain they caused to others, for which there can be no forgiveness,"},{"time":950336,"text":"but the pain they caused to me, there is,\" she said."},{"time":953800,"text":"\"So while I recognize that it would have been better for the world"},{"time":957592,"text":"if Dylan had never been born,"},{"time":960102,"text":"I've decided that it would not have been better for me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":965584,"text":"I thought it was surprising how all of these families had all of these children with all of these problems,"},{"time":972068,"text":"problems that they mostly would have done anything to avoid,"},{"time":975101,"text":"and that they had all found so much meaning in that experience of parenting."},{"time":978920,"text":"And then I thought, all of us who have children"},{"time":982121,"text":"love the children we have, with their flaws."},{"time":984813,"text":"If some glorious angel suddenly descended through my living room ceiling"},{"time":989069,"text":"and offered to take away the children I have"},{"time":991279,"text":"and give me other, better children -- more polite, funnier, nicer, smarter --"},{"time":997873,"text":"I would cling to the children I have and pray away that atrocious spectacle."},{"time":1002978,"text":"And ultimately I feel"},{"time":1004970,"text":"that in the same way that we test flame-retardant pajamas in an inferno"},{"time":1008548,"text":"to ensure they won't catch fire when our child reaches across the stove,"},{"time":1013020,"text":"so these stories of families negotiating these extreme differences"},{"time":1017088,"text":"reflect on the universal experience of parenting,"},{"time":1019769,"text":"which is always that sometimes you look at your child and you think,"},{"time":1023903,"text":"where did you come from?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026092,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028546,"text":"It turns out that while each of these individual differences is siloed --"},{"time":1033521,"text":"there are only so many families dealing with schizophrenia,"},{"time":1036066,"text":"there are only so many families of children who are transgender,"},{"time":1038703,"text":"there are only so many families of prodigies --"},{"time":1040897,"text":"who also face similar challenges in many ways --"},{"time":1043181,"text":"there are only so many families in each of those categories --"},{"time":1045871,"text":"but if you start to think"},{"time":1047303,"text":"that the experience of negotiating difference within your family"},{"time":1050869,"text":"is what people are addressing,"},{"time":1052899,"text":"then you discover that it's a nearly universal phenomenon."},{"time":1056636,"text":"Ironically, it turns out, that it's our differences, and our negotiation of difference,"},{"time":1061271,"text":"that unite us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063699,"text":"I decided to have children while I was working on this project."},{"time":1069013,"text":"And many people were astonished and said,"},{"time":1072129,"text":"\"But how can you decide to have children"},{"time":1073977,"text":"in the midst of studying everything that can go wrong?\""},{"time":1078083,"text":"And I said, \"I'm not studying everything that can go wrong."},{"time":1081313,"text":"What I'm studying is how much love there can be,"},{"time":1084404,"text":"even when everything appears to be going wrong.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1089129,"text":"I thought a lot about the mother of one disabled child I had seen,"},{"time":1094764,"text":"a severely disabled child who died through caregiver neglect."},{"time":1098536,"text":"And when his ashes were interred, his mother said,"},{"time":1101346,"text":"\"I pray here for forgiveness for having been twice robbed,"},{"time":1109380,"text":"once of the child I wanted and once of the son I loved.\""},{"time":1115436,"text":"And I figured it was possible then for anyone to love any child"},{"time":1120072,"text":"if they had the effective will to do so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1122604,"text":"So my husband is the biological father of two children"},{"time":1127629,"text":"with some lesbian friends in Minneapolis."},{"time":1130390,"text":"I had a close friend from college who'd gone through a divorce and wanted to have children."},{"time":1136214,"text":"And so she and I have a daughter,"},{"time":1138112,"text":"and mother and daughter live in Texas."},{"time":1140323,"text":"And my husband and I have a son who lives with us all the time"},{"time":1143562,"text":"of whom I am the biological father,"},{"time":1145946,"text":"and our surrogate for the pregnancy was Laura,"},{"time":1149881,"text":"the lesbian mother of Oliver and Lucy in Minneapolis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152929,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161584,"text":"So the shorthand is five parents of four children in three states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1167048,"text":"And there are people who think that the existence of my family"},{"time":1170404,"text":"somehow undermines or weakens or damages their family."},{"time":1175069,"text":"And there are people who think that families like mine"},{"time":1178697,"text":"shouldn't be allowed to exist."},{"time":1180381,"text":"And I don't accept subtractive models of love, only additive ones."},{"time":1186036,"text":"And I believe that in the same way that we need species diversity"},{"time":1189562,"text":"to ensure that the planet can go on,"},{"time":1191813,"text":"so we need this diversity of affection and diversity of family"},{"time":1196014,"text":"in order to strengthen the ecosphere of kindness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1200695,"text":"The day after our son was born,"},{"time":1203065,"text":"the pediatrician came into the hospital room and said she was concerned."},{"time":1207637,"text":"He wasn't extending his legs appropriately."},{"time":1210770,"text":"She said that might mean that he had brain damage."},{"time":1213679,"text":"In so far as he was extending them, he was doing so asymmetrically,"},{"time":1217040,"text":"which she thought could mean that there was a tumor of some kind in action."},{"time":1220903,"text":"And he had a very large head, which she thought might indicate hydrocephalus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1225686,"text":"And as she told me all of these things,"},{"time":1227316,"text":"I felt the very center of my being pouring out onto the floor."},{"time":1231311,"text":"And I thought, here I had been working for years"},{"time":1233654,"text":"on a book about how much meaning people had found"},{"time":1236203,"text":"in the experience of parenting children who are disabled,"},{"time":1239736,"text":"and I didn't want to join their number."},{"time":1243636,"text":"Because what I was encountering was an idea of illness."},{"time":1246331,"text":"And like all parents since the dawn of time,"},{"time":1248581,"text":"I wanted to protect my child from illness."},{"time":1251927,"text":"And I wanted also to protect myself from illness."},{"time":1255138,"text":"And yet, I knew from the work I had done"},{"time":1257698,"text":"that if he had any of the things we were about to start testing for,"},{"time":1261805,"text":"that those would ultimately be his identity,"},{"time":1264878,"text":"and if they were his identity they would become my identity,"},{"time":1269112,"text":"that that illness was going to take a very different shape as it unfolded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1273269,"text":"We took him to the MRI machine, we took him to the CAT scanner,"},{"time":1276300,"text":"we took this day-old child and gave him over for an arterial blood draw."},{"time":1280298,"text":"We felt helpless."},{"time":1281492,"text":"And at the end of five hours,"},{"time":1282970,"text":"they said that his brain was completely clear"},{"time":1285194,"text":"and that he was by then extending his legs correctly."},{"time":1288204,"text":"And when I asked the pediatrician what had been going on,"},{"time":1291136,"text":"she said she thought in the morning he had probably had a cramp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1295471,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1299036,"text":"But I thought how my mother was right."},{"time":1306869,"text":"I thought, the love you have for your children"},{"time":1310364,"text":"is unlike any other feeling in the world,"},{"time":1313694,"text":"and until you have children, you don't know what it feels like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1319858,"text":"I think children had ensnared me"},{"time":1322179,"text":"the moment I connected fatherhood with loss."},{"time":1325705,"text":"But I'm not sure I would have noticed that"},{"time":1327637,"text":"if I hadn't been so in the thick of this research project of mine."},{"time":1333162,"text":"I'd encountered so much strange love,"},{"time":1336394,"text":"and I fell very naturally into its bewitching patterns."},{"time":1340179,"text":"And I saw how splendor can illuminate even the most abject vulnerabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1346906,"text":"During these 10 years, I had witnessed and learned"},{"time":1350712,"text":"the terrifying joy of unbearable responsibility,"},{"time":1354204,"text":"and I had come to see how it conquers everything else."},{"time":1357736,"text":"And while I had sometimes thought the parents I was interviewing were fools,"},{"time":1362037,"text":"enslaving themselves to a lifetime's journey with their thankless children"},{"time":1366987,"text":"and trying to breed identity out of misery,"},{"time":1369936,"text":"I realized that day that my research had built me a plank"},{"time":1374572,"text":"and that I was ready to join them on their ship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1377986,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1379803,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}